  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "Fix some integer $n$ and define a decreasing sequence in $[1,n)$ by $a_1=n-1$ and, for $k\\geq 2$, letting $a_k$ be the greatest integer in $[1,a_{k-1})$ such that all of the prime factors of $a_k$ are $>n-a_k$.\n\nIs it true that, for sufficiently large $n$, not all of this sequence can be prime?",
